## Hebrew/Aramaic stratum: containment, not conspiracy

**Q1 (qelippot \u0026 sparks).** Šaʿar ha-Gilgulim (Vital, *Hakdamot* 23, 39) and Šaʿar ha-Pesukim are unambiguous that **all souls were included in Adam pre-fall** (כל הנשמות כולם היו כלולים באדם הראשון קודם שחטא) and fell into "the depths of the qelippot" (עומקי הקליפות). The dominant verbs are *malbeshet*, *melapefet*, *shvuyot* — "clothes," "wraps," "captives." This is **ontological encasement**. The Sitra Achra draws *yenikah* (vitality) from trapped sparks, but **no text describes Samael as a strategic adversary running interference on tikkun**. Sefer ha-Bahir predates the developed spark-cosmology entirely. **Verdict: containment YES, strategic adversary NULL.** Confidence high.

**Q9 (Hekhalot sixth-palace).** Hekhalot Rabbati ch. 26 \u0026 Bavli Ḥagigah 14b are explicit: the marble-floor test (אבני שיש טהור) is *nizdaq u-borer im raʾui leyred ba-merkavah* — "examines and tests whether worthy." Guardians (Domiel, Romiel, et al.) **deliberately create the water-illusion as a paternity-of-soul test** ("perhaps you are of the seed of those who kissed the calf"). The worthy ascender is praised (היו משבחין אותו); the unworthy receives iron bars. **The system is not portrayed as compromised — it is portrayed as ruthlessly accurate.** Modern "trap" readings are overlay. Confidence high.

**Q15 (dybbuk petaḥ).** Sefer ha-Ḥezyonot itself contains only ~2–3 dybbuk cases (Damascus woman; 1609 Damascus woman with positive ruaḥ). The dominant sin-type in actual cases is **arayot / adultery producing mamzerim**. The technical doctrine of the *petaḥ* (opening) via *pegam ha-berit* belongs to Šaʿar ha-Gilgulim and Šaʿar Ruaḥ ha-Qodesh, **not Ḥezyonot proper**. Critically, **no passage states that knowledge of the mechanism provides protection** — protection is consistently framed as tiqqun ha-berit, yiḥudim, and teshuvah. Confidence medium on pattern; null result on the knowledge-as-protection thesis.

**Q20 (Temple acoustics).** Mishnah Tamid 3:8 and Bavli Yoma 39b document anomalous distance-effects — High Priest's voice and Temple sounds audible from Jerusalem to Jericho (~28 km). Arakhin 10b–11a describes the *magrefa* with 1,000 *minei zemer* (musical tones), but the **Talmud itself flags this as gozma (exaggeration)**: *we-simanakh — matnita guzma*. Exodus 28:33-35 ties the High Priest's bells explicitly to *protection* ("ve-lo yamut" — that he not die). **No Hebrew or Aramaic text specifies frequencies in Hz**; all modern 432 Hz / Solfeggio claims are baseless overlays on the textual record.

