## Coptic stratum: gnosis with conditions, Authades not Yaldabaoth

**Q8 (Pistis Sophia, Books of Jeu — wrong doors, false light).** Two major corrections to popular accounts. **First, the deceiver of Sophia in Pistis Sophia is Authades (ⲁⲩⲑⲁⲇⲏⲥ), not Yaldabaoth.** Authades emits a "lion-faced light-power" (ⲡⲣⲟⲥⲱⲡⲟⲛ ⲙ̄ⲙⲟⲩⲓ̈) into the lower regions; Sophia, having "ceased to perform the mystery of the thirteenth aeon," gazes down, **mistakes the counterfeit for the light of the Treasury** ("thought it came from the light she had seen from the beginning in the height"), descends, and is robbed of her own light. Second, in PS she falls **only from the 13th material aeon, not from the Pleroma** — contra Apocryphon of John's Sophia. The Books of Jeu (Bruce Codex) describe ascent through 14 aeons requiring at each gate: a **name** (nomen barbarum), a **seal/diagram** (ⲥⲫⲣⲁⲅⲓⲥ), a **cipher** (ⲯⲏⲫⲟⲥ, numerical value), and an invocation commanding archons to *withdraw* (ⲁⲛⲁⲭⲱⲣⲉⲓ). The **Five Seals** of Sethian texts (Ap. John, Trimorphic Protennoia, Gospel of the Egyptians) protect specifically against death — Pronoia "sealed him in the light of the water with five seals, in order that death might not have power over him." Souls lacking the seals are intercepted by the **Virgin of Light**, who reseals them and administers **Sabaoth-Adamas's cup of forgetfulness** (parallel to Lethe), forcing *metensōmatōsis* (reincarnation) until karmic debt clears. The afterlife geography ascends: Outer Darkness → Chaos → Sphere of Fate → 12 Aeons → 13th Aeon → Way of the Midst → Place of the Right → Treasury of Light. Confidence high on narrative; medium on exact Sahidic morphology (worked from Mead/Schmidt-MacDermot via secondary sources).

**Q12 (Nag Hammadi — gnosis as liberation mechanism).** Catalog of every NHC text where knowledge is the operative mechanism, tagged Self / Architecture / Source:

| Text | Knowledge type |
|---|---|
| Gospel of Truth | Source + Self ("ignorance brought terror; the Father's name unspoken") |
| Thomas log. 3, 50, 67 | Self ("know yourselves"; "we came from the light"; "whoever knows the all but not himself lacks everything") |
| Apocryphon of John | Self + Architecture + Source (paradigmatic all-three) |
| Gospel of Philip | Self + Source ("knowledge is freedom; ignorance is slavery") |
| Treatise on Resurrection | Self ("recovering what one was at the beginning") |
| Authoritative Teaching | Self + Source (learning about "the Inscrutable") |
| Tripartite Tractate | All three (Valentinian pneumatic predestination) |
| Hypostasis of the Archons | Architecture + Self ("root of truth"; Samael exposed as "god of the blind") |
| Allogenes | Source apophatic ("better not to know than to know falsely") |
| Zostrianos | All three + baptismal ascent |
| Three Steles of Seth | Source only (pure liturgical praise; no archons) |
| Trimorphic Protennoia | All three + Five Seals |
| Theodotus 78.2 (extra-NHC) | All four explicit categories — "who we were, what we have become; where we were, whither thrown; whither we hasten, from what redeemed" |

**Critical null-results:** (1) **No NHC text isolates gnosis as the *sole* mechanism** — Philip pairs it with bridal-chamber sacrament, Ap. John with Five Seals, Theodotus explicitly: "it is not only the washing that is liberating, *but* the knowledge." The popular "Gnosticism = salvation by knowledge alone" claim is overstated. (2) **Thomas log. 67 explicitly subordinates Architecture-knowledge to Self-knowledge.** (3) **Allogenes and Three Steles of Seth contain virtually no archon-system content** — refuting "all Gnostic texts are anti-cosmic dualist." (4) **PS's Sophia is not Pleromatic** and her deceiver is Authades, not Yaldabaoth — a doubled deception via secondary emanation. Confidence high.

